eploy-side path to match the PromptClaw repo structure. The use of `RecordingEventStore` and `RecordingMemory` mocks is consistent with existing patterns.\\n\\n## Security\\nThe authentication gate is implemented as a dependency that runs before the endpoint logic. While the comparison is a simple string match (as noted in the spec, T-010 owns the hardened comparison), it correctly secures the endpoints when a token is provided. No secrets were committed; the tests use placeholder \\\"secret\\\" strings.\\n\\n## Quality\\nThe code is clean, well-documented, and passes all tests. Regression anchors (`test_first_boot.py`, `test_governor_integration.py`, etc.) remain green, ensuring no side effects on startup or resource management.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- None.\\n\\n## Verdict: PASS\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\nThe decision to keep tests in the root `tests/` directory to align with `pyproject.toml` is correct for this repository's layout. Coverage is solid, and the 503 fallback paths for missing deploy-side dependencies are well-tested.\\n\",\"file_path\":\"sdp/verification/t-005@20260502t001347z-verify.md\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T00:54:09.978Z\",\"tool_id\":\"write_file_1777683249963_0\",\"status\":\"success\"}\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 1m 17s / 30m 0s\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T00:54:11.549Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I will commit the verification report with a descriptive\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T00:54:11.826Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" message.\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T00:54:11.985Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777683251985_0\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"git add sdp/verification/t-005@20260502t001347z-verify.md && git commit -m \\\"verify(T-005@20260502T001347Z): PASS\\\" && git status\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-02T00:54:12.2