sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md:1:# SDP Telemetry Cost Model
sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md:5:This reference is the operator-facing cost model for PromptClaw SDP telemetry. It covers two active cost surfaces:
sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md:7:- SDP agent token accounting: historical telemetry, static per-million-token pricing, p50/p90 prediction, admission rejection, and safe worker concurrency.
sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md:82:No fixed per-call USD charge is added to SDP token calls. SDP token cost is variable-only: input tokens plus output tokens priced by model.
sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md:84:SDP capacity planning keeps a token reserve before estimating worker capacity. The default `selector_reserve_fraction` is `0.20`, meaning 20 percent of the provider token limit is held back from concurrency calculations.
