sdp/runner.log:212:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-05-03T01:51:51.295Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task frac-0086\n\n**Task:** Deepen test_listener_review from depth 1 to depth 2: Simple: one-path implementation, functions produce meaningful output, end-to-end works\n**Tier:** T2\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nSimple: one-path implementation, functions produce meaningful output, end-to-end works\n\nHint: Implement the simplest working version of each function. One algorithm path, no edge cases. The system should work end-to-end with this module.\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n3. **Review specification** (if T2/T3):\n   Read `specs/frac-0086-spec.md`\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/frac-0086-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — frac-0086\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
