d), and asserts the row reaches `done`.\\n\\n# Technical Approach\\n- Update `GenerationQueue.__init__` to accept `client: Any | None = None`, `cache: Any | None = None`, `budget: Any | None = None`, `storage: Any | None = None`, `max_concurrent: int = 1`.\\n- Implement `process_one()` (or `run_worker(run_once=True)`) on `GenerationQueue` that:\\n  1. Calls `dequeue()`. Returns early if `None`.\\n  2. If `client` is present, calls `client.generate(item.payload)`.\\n  3. If `storage` is present, calls `storage.save(result, item.payload)`.\\n  4. Calls `mark_done(item.id)` on success.\\n  5. Catches exceptions and calls `mark_failed(item.id)`.\\n- Add an integration test `test_generation_queue_integration_worker_loop_success` using a fake client and fake storage that enqueues a request, runs `process_one()`, and verifies the row reaches `done`.\\n\\n# Edge Cases\\n- Dependencies like `cache` and `budget` do not exist yet, so they must be optional (`None` by default) and ignored if absent.\\n- `process_one` handles transient failures by calling `mark_failed()`.\\n\\n# Acceptance Criteria\\n1. `GenerationQueue` constructor accepts pipeline dependencies (`client`, `storage`, etc).\\n   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_generation_queue.py -k \\\"constructor\\\" -q`\\n2. `process_one` successfully processes a queued item, generates audio, stores it, and marks it done.\\n   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_generation_queue.py::test_integration_worker_loop_success -q`\\nEOF\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T03:57:28.800Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777262248800_1\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"cat << 'EOF' > tests/test_integration_generation_queue.py\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom senseweave.generation.queue import GenerationQueue, QUEUED, DONE, FAILED\\nfrom senseweave.generation.storage import GenerationStorage\\nimport sqlite3\\n\\nclass FakeClient:\\n    def generate(self, request):\\n        return {\\